<h2 ><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" height="25" width="25"/><a href="#">  &nbsp; About Department Plants Protection</a></h2>
<br />
<p> The Department of Plant Pests and Diseases Science was founded in 1972 as a department within the Faculty of Agriculture, Bogor Agricultural University, which then changed its name to Department of Plant Protection in 2006.  Since its establishment the department has been playing an important role in imparting agricultural education and conducting basic and applied research in the field of plant pathology, agricultural entomology, rodentology, and plant health management.
<br />
Currently, the department has 41 faculty members with high competence in various aspects of plant health sciences such as insect biosystematics, insect bionomy and ecology, insect physiology and toxicology, insect pathology, biological control, vertebrate pests, plant mycology, bacteriology, virology, and nematology.
<br />
The department offers undergraduate program for students interested in plant protection major or minor and graduate programs for advance degrees in Plant Pathology and Entomology.  The graduates of the department are serving in public and private sectors institutions on key position within the country.  <a href=""> &nbsp;Read more >> </a>  </p>


